function onTick() Fuel = input.getNumber(7) Switch = input.getNumber(8) Yellow = input.getNumber(9) Red = input.getNumber(10) output.setBool(3, P2) output.setBool(4, P1) inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) Press = input.getNumber(1) P1 = Press and Zone(inputX, inputY, 0, 7, 16, 8) P2 = Press and Zone(inputX, inputY, 16, 7, 15, 8) Ratio = Fuel/MaxF
if 0 == Tick and MaxF < Fuel then MaxF = Fuel end if 0 == Tick then Fuel1 = Fuel end Tick = Tick + 1 if 7 == Tick then Fuel2 = Fuel Use = ((Fuel1-Fuel2)*10) Tick = 0 end
if Ratio <= Red then Red = 250 Green = 0 elseif Red < Ratio and Ratio <= Yellow then Red = 100 Green = 100 else Red = 0 Green = 100 end
Cons = Use*0.05 + Cons*0.95 if 0.0001 <= Cons then Time = Fuel/Cons elseif Cons <= -0.0001 then Time = math.abs((MaxF-Fuel)/Cons) else Time = 0 end end
function Zone(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear()
screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, 32, 7) screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawTextBox(1, 1, 32, 7, "Fuel", 0, 0)
if Switch == 1 then screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRectF(0, 7, 16, 9) screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawTextBox(1, 8, 15, 8, "Gas", 0, 0) else screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRect(0, 7, 16, 8) screen.drawTextBox(1, 8, 15, 8, "Gas", 0, 0) end if Switch == 2 then screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRectF(16, 7, 16, 9) screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawTextBox(17, 8, 15, 8, "Use", 0, 0) else screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRect(16, 7, 15, 8) screen.drawTextBox(17, 8, 15, 8, "Use", 0, 0) end
if Switch == 1 then screen.setColor(Red, Green, 0) screen.drawRectF(0, 16, 32, 7) screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) if 10 <= Fuel then screen.drawTextBox(0, 17, 32, 5, string.format("%.0f", Fuel), 0, 0) else screen.drawTextBox(0, 17, 32, 5, string.format("%.2f", Fuel), 0, 0) end screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawTextBox(0, 25, 32, 5, string.format("%.2f", math.abs(Cons)), 0, 0) else screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) screen.drawRectF(0, 16, 32, 7) screen.drawTextBox(0, 25, 32, 5, "HH:MM", 0, 0) screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) if 100 <= Time/(60*60) then screen.drawTextBox(0, 17, 32, 5, "+99:59", 0, 0) else screen.drawTextBox(0, 17, 32, 5, string.format("%.0f:%.0f", ((Time/(60*60))-((Time/(60*60))%1)), Time/60%60), 0, 0) end end end

sw = input.getBool(1)
if sw~=onoff then tick = tick+1 end
if sw==true then if tick>don then tick = 0 onoff = sw num = von end else if tick>doff then tick = 0 onoff = sw num = voff end end
output.setNumber(1, num) end

--artificial horizon
--useful abbreviation pi2=2*math.pi pi=math.pi sin=math.sin cos=math.cos sdL=screen.drawLine ssC=screen.setColor igN=input.getNumber pgB=property.getBool
NM=pgB("Night Mode")
function onTick() --reads input data Tilt_front=igN(1) Tilt_right=igN(2) Tilt_up=igN(3) OFFSET=igN(4)
--determines the roll angle from -pi to pi if Tilt_up>=0 then RollAngle=-pi2*Tilt_right elseif Tilt_up<0 and Tilt_right>=0 then RollAngle=-pi2*(0.5-Tilt_right) elseif Tilt_up<0 and Tilt_right<0 then RollAngle=-pi2*(-0.5-Tilt_right) end --determines the pitch angle from -pi/2 to pi/2 PitchAngle=pi2*Tilt_front end
function onDraw() sW=screen.getWidth() sH=screen.getHeight()
if not NM then --creates background ssC(150,150,150) for i=-450,450 do if i<0 then --selects colour depending on whether bars are in the sky or pointing to the ground ssC(0,20,240) elseif i>=0 then ssC(27,18,9) --57,38,19 end temp_X=sW/2+sin(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/450*sin(RollAngle) --pi*sH/18 comes from 1/2*(2*r*pi)/18 r=sH temp_Y=sH/2+cos(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/450*cos(RollAngle) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X+cos(RollAngle)*sW,temp_Y-sin(RollAngle)*sW) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X-cos(RollAngle)*sW,temp_Y+sin(RollAngle)*sW) end end
--creates bars at 10 degree intervals for i=-18,18 do if i<0 then --selects colour depending on whether bars are in the sky or pointing to the ground if not NM then ssC(200,200,200) else ssC(0,200,0) end elseif i>=0 then if not NM then ssC(200,200,200) else ssC(0,200,0) end end temp_X=sW/2+sin(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/18*sin(RollAngle) --pi*sH/18 comes from 1/2*(2*r*pi)/18 with r=sH temp_Y=sH/2+cos(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/18*cos(RollAngle) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X+cos(RollAngle)*15,temp_Y-sin(RollAngle)*15) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X-cos(RollAngle)*15,temp_Y+sin(RollAngle)*15) end
--creates bars at 5 degree intervals for i=-36,36 do if i<0 then --selects colour depending on whether bars are in the sky or pointing to the ground if not NM then ssC(200,200,200) else ssC(0,200,0) end elseif i>=0 then if not NM then ssC(200,200,200) else ssC(0,200,0) end end temp_X=sW/2+sin(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/36*sin(RollAngle) --pi*sH/18 comes from 1/2*(2*r*pi)/18 with r=sH temp_Y=sH/2+cos(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle+i*pi*OFFSET/36*cos(RollAngle) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X+cos(RollAngle)*7,temp_Y-sin(RollAngle)*7) sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X-cos(RollAngle)*7,temp_Y+sin(RollAngle)*7) end
--defines the horizon temp_X=sW/2+sin(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle --sH*PitchAngle comes from 1/2*(2*r*pi)*angle/pi with r=sH temp_Y=sH/2+cos(RollAngle)*OFFSET*PitchAngle if not NM then ssC(200,200,200) else ssC(0,200,0) end sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X+cos(RollAngle)*sW,temp_Y-sin(RollAngle)*sW) -- 15 is half the width of the bars sdL(temp_X,temp_Y,temp_X-cos(RollAngle)*sW,temp_Y+sin(RollAngle)*sW)
if not NM then ssC(200,200,0) else ssC(40,40,0) end for i=0,360,22.5 do sdL(sW/2+8*cos(i/360*pi2),sH/2-8*sin(i/360*pi2),sW/2+10*cos(i/360*pi2),sH/2-10*sin(i/360*pi2)) end if not NM then ssC(200,0,0) else ssC(40,0,0) end sdL(sW/2+6*cos(RollAngle-pi/2),sH/2-6*sin(RollAngle-pi/2),sW/2+8*cos(RollAngle-pi/2),sH/2-8*sin(RollAngle-pi/2))
--creates cross-hair if not NM then ssC(200,0,200) else ssC(40,0,40) end if sW<=64 then diff=3 else diff=0 end sdL(sW/2,sH/2,sW/2+1,sH/2) sdL(sW/2-5,sH/2,sW/2-(20-diff),sH/2) sdL(sW/2+5,sH/2,sW/2+(20-diff),sH/2) sdL(sW/2-5,sH/2,sW/2-5,sH/2+2) sdL(sW/2+5,sH/2,sW/2+5,sH/2+2) end

PDeg=mf(Deg/Step)*Step PStep=ma(PDeg-Deg)/Step*StepPix sdTB(W/2-PStep-10,H-Hpos-3,20,8,value(PDeg),0,0) screen.drawLine(W/2-PStep,H-Hpos+8,W/2-PStep,H-Hpos+4) if not NM then ssC(RR,GG,BB) else ssC(0,200,0) end screen.drawLine(W/2-PStep+StepPix/2,H-Hpos+8,W/2-PStep+StepPix/2,H-Hpos+6) screen.drawLine(W/2-PStep-StepPix/2,H-Hpos+8,W/2-PStep-StepPix/2,H-Hpos+6) for i=1,mc(W/StepPix) do sdTB(W/2-PStep-i*StepPix-10,H-Hpos-3,20,8,value(PDeg-i*Step),0,0) screen.drawLine(W/2-PStep-i*StepPix,H-Hpos+8,W/2-PStep-i*StepPix,H-Hpos+4) if not NM then ssC(RR,GG,BB) else ssC(0,200,0) end screen.drawLine(W/2-PStep-i*StepPix-StepPix/2,H-Hpos+8,W/2-PStep-i*StepPix-StepPix/2,H-Hpos+6) end
if not NM then ssC(200,0,0) else ssC(40,0,0) end screen.drawTriangleF(W/2-3,H-Hpos+9,W/2+4,H-Hpos+9,W/2,H-Hpos+5)
end end
function round(Value) a,b=math.modf(Value) if b>=0.5 then return a+1 else return a end end
function value(V) if V>360 then V=V-360 elseif V<0 then V=360+V end
if not NM then ssC(200,0,200) else ssC(40,0,40) end
if V==360 or V==0 then return "N" elseif V==90 then return "O" elseif V==180 then return "S" elseif V==270 then return "W" else if not NM then ssC(RR,GG,BB) else ssC(0,200,0) end return sf("%.0f",V) end end
